        "timestamp": "2019-03-15 14:20:23.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\nSetting jinja2_native = True and making it work with resources playbook was impossible to do (without moving the shell one-liner into separate template and do more jinja2 tricks - no tested - ugly anyway)\n\nFix was this (which I actually did try before but it did not work with ansible 2.6.3) but now it works - ugly? yes! retarded? definitively! But it works!\n\nBartek had idea to rewrite json value into yaml and rewrite module to accept python structure (?) instead of string - I did not like the idea to edit json file (daemon.json) by firstly rewrite the changes to yaml, so the module will convert it back to json ... that kills copy-paste feature of finding some config on docker website and drop it to ansible - you msut first rewrite it to yaml (yuck).",
        "patchset_number": 6
      },
